  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "I found a whole page of small events from this month that never made it into a full entry, so here they are, all together.",
      "zh": "我發現這個月有一整頁的小事件從來沒被我寫成完整的一篇，所以這次全部一起補上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our neighbor's cat gave birth to four tiny kittens last week, and honestly, they might be the cutest things I have ever seen.",
      "zh": "我們鄰居的貓上星期生了四隻小小貓，老實說，牠們大概是我見過最可愛的東西。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William tried to bathe one of the kittens in the bathroom sink, and the kitten was not the slightest bit grateful for the help.",
      "zh": "William 想在浴室洗手台幫其中一隻小貓洗澡，那隻小貓一點都不領情。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the corner store, I got a small bug bite on my finger while reaching for a candy bar on the bottom shelf.",
      "zh": "在轉角雜貨店，我伸手拿最下面架子上的一條巧克力棒時，手指被小蟲咬了一口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I still bought the candy bar anyway, since a bug bite seemed like a reasonable price for something that sweet.",
      "zh": "我還是把那條巧克力棒買了，畢竟為了那麼甜的東西被咬一口好像也算合理。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad borrowed the neighbor's ladder last weekend to fix a loose window blind, and somehow it took him three separate tries.",
      "zh": "爸爸上週末跟鄰居借了梯子去修一片鬆脫的百葉窗，不知怎麼地他試了整整三次才成功。"
    },
    {
      "en": "During dinner that same night, he had one small glass of beer and told a long, dull story about ladders from his own childhood.",
      "zh": "同一晚吃晚餐的時候，他喝了一小杯啤酒，講了一個很無聊的、關於他小時候梯子的長故事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William rang his bicycle bell nonstop the whole way to school on Monday, until Mom finally told him it counted as noise pollution.",
      "zh": "星期一去學校的路上，William 一路不停按腳踏車鈴，媽媽最後跟他說這已經算是噪音污染了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice got a haircut that made her look, in her own words, \"ten percent more mature and ninety percent the same amount of dramatic.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 剪了一個新髮型，用她自己的話說，看起來「成熟了百分之十，戲劇化程度還是一樣的百分之九十」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our English teacher mentioned that learning any foreign language gets easier once you stop being afraid of sounding silly.",
      "zh": "我們英文老師提到，只要不再害怕聽起來很傻，學任何一種外語都會變得比較容易。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My pencil lead broke three times during a single math quiz, which I have decided to blame entirely on bad luck, not my own handwriting.",
      "zh": "我的鉛筆芯在一次數學小考中斷了三次，我決定完全怪罪運氣不好，而不是我自己的字跡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William got in a small fight with a classmate over whose turn it was to use a red crayon, and both boys apologized within five minutes.",
      "zh": "William 跟一個同學為了輪到誰用紅蠟筆吵了一小架，兩個男生五分鐘內就互相道歉了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the night market again, we tried a slice of guava, which William said tasted like \"a very confused apple.\"",
      "zh": "我們又去了一次夜市，試吃了一片芭樂，William 說吃起來像「一顆非常迷惘的蘋果」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia bought a small pot of fresh herbs for the kitchen window, saying homegrown flavor is always worth the effort.",
      "zh": "Sophia 買了一小盆新鮮香草放在廚房窗邊，說自己種出來的味道永遠值得那份努力。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I finally learned to peel a whole potato without cutting my own finger, which Sophia treated like a genuine graduation ceremony.",
      "zh": "我終於學會削整顆馬鈴薯皮而不切到自己的手指，Sophia 把這當成一場真正的畢業典禮來慶祝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That is everything from this month's leftover notes, and my notebook finally feels properly caught up for once.",
      "zh": "以上就是這個月所有補記的小事，我的筆記本這次終於感覺真正跟上進度了。"
    }
  ],
